<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - REMOVE - AUXILIARY
        SECTION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="8">
        <title>AUXILIARY SECTION</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>There can be different bolt lengths; note their location.</para>
            <para>Auxiliary sections can be removed either with the transmission in the horizontal position or the
                vertical position.
            </para>
            <para>Auxiliary countershaft retaining straps may be installed to hold the countershafts in place. Auxiliary
                can be removed without straps, use caution.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>To remove the auxiliary section in the horizontal position.</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four (4) bolts, auxiliary countershaft rear bearing cover, gasket and rear
                    bearing shim (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302024">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302024" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302024" filename="../figg13/G1302024.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 24. Remove Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the auxiliary countershaft retaining covers with two 3/8" NC x 1" and one 3/8"
                    NC x 1-1/2" clean bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302025">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302025" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302025" filename="../figg13/G1302025.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 25. Auxiliary Countershaft Retaining Covers</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not use an air gun. Tighten by hand until the bolts are snug.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts from the auxiliary section housing that attach the front
                    section to the auxiliary section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302026">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302026" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302026" filename="../figg13/G1302026.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 26. Remove Retaining Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the two (2) longest bolts in the housing flange tapped holes. Tighten evenly to
                    move the auxiliary section away from the front box. Go far enough to break the gasket seal (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302026">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bolts from the tapped holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach an auxiliary section hanger bracket to the top of the auxiliary section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302027">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302027" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302027" filename="../figg13/G1302027.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 27. Attach Lifting Chain</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a lifting chain to the auxiliary section hanger bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302027">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Move assembly to the rear until auxiliary section is free.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the gasket and clean all mounting surfaces of gasket material.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>To remove the auxiliary section in the vertical position.</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With blocks under the clutch housing to prevent input shaft damage, place transmission
                    in the vertical position, clutch housing down.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four (4) bolts and the auxiliary countershaft rear bearing cover, gasket, and
                    rear bearing shim (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302028">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302028" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302028" filename="../figg13/G1302028.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 28. Remove Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install auxiliary countershaft retaining straps with two 3/8" NC x 1" and one 3/8" NC x
                    1-1/2" clean bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302029">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302029" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302029" filename="../figg13/G1302029.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 29. Install Retaining Straps</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not use an air gun. Tighten by hand until the bolts are snug.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts that attach the front section to the auxiliary section (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302030">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302030" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302030" filename="../figg13/G1302030.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 30. Remove Retaining Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a steel bar through the yoke (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302031">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1302031" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1302031" filename="../figg13/G1302031.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 31. Steel Bar Through Yoke</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a lifting chain to the steel bar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302031">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift assembly from the front section.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the gasket and clean all mounting surfaces of gasket material.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
